    "body": "```\nerror: could not find start lang item\n\n\nMiri caused an ICE during evaluation. Here's the interpreter backtrace at the time of the panic:\nnote: the place in the program where the ICE was triggered\n  |\n  = note: (no span available)\n\nerror: aborting due to 1 previous error; 1 warning emitted\n```\n\n\n\n\nThere are two kinds of entry point in miri.\nhttps://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/blob/cc2d666003657a5adf4b5dc7e742888310295e97/src/bin/miri.rs#L94\n\n\nBased on main entry https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/b5a50f3092d9b4bfaa0c152dad567928cec129d2/osdk/src/base_crate/main.rs.template#L9 , I got the error above. \n\nSince `#[start]` has been removed since  https://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/blob/cc2d666003657a5adf4b5dc7e742888310295e97/src/eval.rs#L403 , so we can't wrote \nhttps://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/ea47dca295aa2760a028a584d2ef9b8b13292549/osdk/src/base_crate/main.rs.template#L10 any more.\n\n\nFor no_std crate, the solution is to use miri entry as follows\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(miri)]\n#[unsafe(no_mangle)]\nfn miri_start(argc: isize, argv: *const *const u8) -> isize {\n```",
